  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment on Israel and Judah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Hear this, O priests!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Take heed, O house of Israel!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Give ear, O royal house!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For this judgment is against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because you have been a snare at Mizpah,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a net spread out on Tabor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rebels are deep in slaughter;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but I will chastise them all.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I know all about Ephraim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2469
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel is not hidden from Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For now, O Ephraim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have turned to prostitution;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Israel is defiled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their deeds do not permit them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to return to their God,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for a spirit of prostitution is within them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they do not know the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel’s arrogance testifies against them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Israel and Ephraim stumble in their iniquity;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even Judah stumbles with them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They go with their flocks and herds",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to seek the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but they do not find Him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has withdrawn Himself from them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They have been unfaithful to the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for they have borne illegitimate children.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Now the New Moon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2470
          },
          {
            "text": "will devour them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "along with their land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blow the ram’s horn in Gibeah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the trumpet in Ramah;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "raise the battle cry in Beth-aven:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2471
          },
          {
            "text": "Lead on, O Benjamin!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim will be laid waste",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the day of rebuke.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Among the tribes of Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I proclaim what is certain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The princes of Judah",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are like those who move boundary stones;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2472
          },
          {
            "text": "I will pour out My fury",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "upon them like water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim is oppressed, crushed in judgment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for he is determined to follow worthless idols.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2473
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So I am like a moth to Ephraim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and like decay to the house of Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When Ephraim saw his sickness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Judah his wound,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "then Ephraim turned to Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sent to the great king.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2474
          },
          {
            "text": "But he cannot cure you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or heal your wound.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I am like a lion to Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and like a young lion to the house of Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, even I, will tear them to pieces",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and then go away.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will carry them off",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where no one can rescue them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I will return to My place",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until they admit their guilt and seek My face;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in their affliction they will earnestly seek Me.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2469,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verses 5, 9, 11, 12, 13, and 14",
        "reference": {
